# Fix: align EVM frame memory stipend with zk_evm
#
# Closes the vm2 vs zk_evm state divergence documented in:
#   - security-review/fuzz-crash-id000000-evm-stipend.md
#   - security-review/fuzz-crash-id000001-evm-stipend.md
#   - security-review/fuzz-crash-id000002-evm-stipend.md
#   - security-review/fuzz-crash-id000003-evm-stipend.md
#
# Root cause: vm2 keyed the new frame's heap/aux-heap stipend on `is_evm`,
# which is only set when the deployer-storage version byte is 0x02 *and* the
# construction-state predicate (`is_constructed != is_constructor_call`) is
# satisfied. zk_evm keys the stipend on `code_version_byte == 0x02` alone
# (zk_evm/src/opcodes/execution/far_call.rs:660-664), independent of whether
# the call masks to the default AA.
#
# Fix: introduce a separate `is_evm_blob_format` flag in `WorldDiff::decommit`
# (set whenever `code_info_bytes[0] == 0x02`, regardless of mask) and plumb it
# through `far_call.rs` -> `vm.push_frame` -> `Callframe::new`, where it now
# drives the stipend selection. `is_evm_interpreter` retains its prior meaning
# in `far_call.rs` (gates `is_static && !is_evm_interpreter` and the
# `call_type` encoding), exactly mirroring zk_evm's split between
# `code_version_byte` (stipend) and `call_to_evm_emulator` (static / call_type).
#
# Validation:
#   - `crates/vm2/src/tests/divergence_regressions.rs::
#      far_call_to_unconstructed_evm_downgrades_stipend_versus_zk_evm` now
#     asserts NEW_EVM_FRAME_MEMORY_STIPEND (57344) and passes after the fix.
#   - All 49 vm2 lib tests pass under the default feature set.
#   - The 4 single_instruction_test precompile failures observed locally
#     (`Should use arbitrary heap, not fresh heap in testing.`) are
#     pre-existing on the popzxc-airbender-eravm branch and unrelated.
#
# Apply with:  git apply security-review/stipend-fix.patch

